NOTE — probe_dooriv_witness_ratio_growth.py — verdict + sampling caveat

OBJECT: witness ratio R(n) = |eta(b*)| / C(b*), where b* = argmax_b |eta_b| (the prize-worst
frequency) and C = the small-ball max-window-count functional. This instantiates the
unbounded-family-ratio hypothesis of kernel 434795470 (_DoorIVArgmaxDecouplingNoControl): a uniform
control |eta_b| <= K*C_b forces K >= R(n), so if R(n) grows, no absolute constant K works.

RESULT (EXACT complex sums, proper mu_n < F_p*, p >> n^3, p == 1 mod n, never n=q-1):
  n=16  p=65537       R=1.153   (full enum over all b)
  n=32  p=1048609     R=2.873   (full enum)
  n=64  p=16777153    R=8.289   (full enum)
  n=128 p=268437889   R=13.223  (full enum)
  n=256 p=4294968833  R=11.201  (b* SAMPLED: uniform 200k of ~4.3B b)
  fit R(n) ~ n^0.876 (clean, monotone on the full-enum points 16..128).

CAVEAT (honesty): at n=256 the b-set was uniformly SUB-SAMPLED (200000 of p-1 ~ 4.3e9), so b* there
is a sampled lower-bound on the true argmax, and C(b*) at the sampled b* (=7) is noisier than the
full-enum points. The true |eta(b*)| at n=256 can only be LARGER (argmax over a superset), so the true
R(256) is a LOWER bound here; the growth conclusion is conservative, not inflated. The decisive
evidence is the monotone full-enum chain n=16..128: R = 1.15 -> 2.87 -> 8.29 -> 13.22, growing
super-linearly in sqrt(n) (R/sqrt(n) rises 0.29 -> 1.17).

VERDICT: the witness ratio R(n) GROWS with n. The unbounded-ratio hypothesis is EMPIRICALLY
INSTANTIATED for the small-ball window functional => the small-ball / window-occupancy control is
DEAD (no absolute constant), not merely decoupled. Refutation-with-mechanism. NO CORE bound — this
bounds a CANDIDATE LEVER out of existence, it does not bound M(n). CORE stays OPEN.
